    <body>
        <p>Lets you set the default look for objects. For example, let's say you draw a rectangle on <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">an image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">a frame</MadCap:conditionalText> and make formatting changes to the shape (e.g., color, border, shading). If you then select this object and set it as the default look, future rectangles will initially contain these same settings when you draw them. This option is enabled only if a single object is selected. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Appearance/Look_of_Objects/Setting_the_Default_Look_for_Objects_Capture.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Setting the Default Look for Objects</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Appearance/Look_of_Objects/Setting_the_Default_Look_for_Objects_Mimic.htm">Setting the Default Look for Objects</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
    </body>
